# Embedded Systems (Draft)

*This course is currently under development. Detailed content, including lecture slides and lab manuals, will be uploaded soon.*

---

## 📘 Course Description
This course provides a comprehensive introduction to the design and implementation of embedded systems. Students will gain hands-on experience with popular microcontrollers, learning to interface with sensors, actuators, and communication protocols.

### Key Topics
- **Introduction to Microcontrollers**: Memory architectures, GPIO, and interrupts.
- **Real-Time Concepts**: Task scheduling and RTOS fundamentals.
- **Communication Protocols**: Deep dive into I2C, SPI, and UART.
- **Embedded Security**: Secure boot and hardware-based trust.
- **Low-Power Optimization**: Techniques for battery-powered IoT devices.

